channel.topic:
Design a farm that will yield a plentiful harvest!
Challenge dates: September 1, 2020 – September 14, 2020 at 6 PM PT

messages.content:
:carrot: **Plentiful Farm Build Challenge** :potato:

Your inventory is stocked with resources. Your crafting table is ready to fashion some tools. And your buildplates have acreage. Till the land—it’s time to get planting!

:diamond_hoe: **Design a farm that will yield a plentiful harvest!** Use any of your favorite foods, seeds, items, and blocks!

Be resourceful and consider your farm’s efficiency to produce a fruitful harvest. Don’t be afraid to stray from traditional farm ideas either! Maybe your farm’s terrain is unique and yields something so ripe we never even thought of it. *We look forward to seeing what you sow!* :wheat_seeds: 

:timer: Challenge dates: September 1, 2020 – September 14, 2020 at 6 PM PT

__Challenge Guidelines__
:earth: Your creation must be built entirely by you and in Minecraft Earth.
:crafting_table: Your build must be a brand new creation, crafted just for this challenge.
:buildplate: Build your imagination! Challenge theme is open to interpretation and buildplate size won’t be a factor in judging.
:sign: Post your images or video submission and buildplate share link in #plentiful-farm-challenge by the end date. Feel free to ask a Moderator to pin it!
:challenges_og: Submissions may be used in social media posts.
:fast_parrot: Have fun!

The Rainbow Factory

Buildplate share:  https://www.minecraft.net/earth/buildplateshare?id=bz7fo2mmhff

Because we could all use a little brightness in our lives  :)

To harvest plants, place a water source block on the topmost dark oak stair on each of the three sections (carrots, wheat, cornflowers). Let the water work through for a minute or two and then collect the drops from the collection pools at the front of the build plate. Then you should have a rainbow in your hot bar!

To collect concrete, tap the solid concrete block at the bottom of each concrete powder tower. You can tap and hold, just be sure you’re pointing straight forward or you might harvest something other than concrete.


YouTube video of harvesting:  https://youtu.be/59ggpJgL-6w
